Use the standard library
>>> tostring of 42 
"42"
>>> tostring of 3.140000 
"3.140000"
>>> toarray of "Hi" 
[72, 105]
>>> toarray of "ABC" 
[65, 66, 67]
>>> toint of "100" 
100
>>> tofloat of "3.14" 
3.140000
This is how to digits of n:
   Remember that s is tostring of n
   The answer is s's length
Now you know
>>> digits of 7 
1
>>> digits of 100 
3
>>> digits of 123456 
6